---
---
<section class="py-24 border-b border-b1" id="how-it-works">
  <div class="max-w-[1200px] mx-auto px-5 md:px-10">
    <span class="inline-block text-[11px] font-bold tracking-[0.1em] uppercase text-accent mb-2.5">How it works</span>
    <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-t1 leading-[1.15] mb-3">Calculating overtime pay</h2>
    <p class="text-[15px] text-t2 max-w-[600px] leading-[1.7] mb-10">The math is simple once you know your state's threshold and multiplier. Here's the full breakdown.</p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 md:gap-12">
      <div>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-8">
          <div class="grid grid-cols-[36px_1fr] gap-4 items-start">
            <div class="w-9 h-9 bg-s2 border border-b1 rounded-lg text-sm font-bold text-t1 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">1</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-t1 mb-1.5 tracking-tight">Find your overtime rate</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-t2 leading-relaxed">Multiply your regular hourly rate by the overtime multiplier. US federal default is <strong>1.5× (time and a half)</strong>. Example: $15.00 × 1.5 = $22.50/hr overtime rate.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-[36px_1fr] gap-4 items-start">
            <div class="w-9 h-9 bg-s2 border border-b1 rounded-lg text-sm font-bold text-t1 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">2</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-t1 mb-1.5 tracking-tight">Multiply by overtime hours</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-t2 leading-relaxed">Take your overtime rate and multiply by hours worked past the threshold. Example: $22.50/hr × 8 OT hours = <strong class="text-green">$180 overtime pay</strong>.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-[36px_1fr] gap-4 items-start">
            <div class="w-9 h-9 bg-s2 border border-b1 rounded-lg text-sm font-bold text-t1 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">3</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-t1 mb-1.5 tracking-tight">Add your regular pay</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-t2 leading-relaxed">Regular pay = 40 hours × base rate. Add both for your total gross. Example: $600 regular + $180 overtime = <strong class="text-[#6366F1]">$780 total</strong>.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-col gap-6">
        <div class="bg-[#0D1117] border border-[#30363D] rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-lg">
          <div class="bg-[#161B22] border-b border-[#30363D] px-4 py-2.5 text-xs text-[#8B949E] font-medium flex items-center gap-3">
            <div class="flex gap-1.5">
              <span class="w-[9px] h-[9px] rounded-full bg-[#FF5F56] opacity-80"></span>
              <span class="w-[9px] h-[9px] rounded-full bg-[#FFBD2E] opacity-80"></span>
              <span class="w-[9px] h-[9px] rounded-full bg-[#27C93F] opacity-80"></span>
            </div>
            overtime-formula.js
          </div>
          <div class="p-5">
            <code class="block font-mono text-[13.5px] leading-[1.8] text-[#E6EDF3]">
              <span class="text-[#8B949E] italic">// 1. Overtime rate</span><br/>
              otRate = hourlyRate * multiplier<br/>
              &nbsp;<br/>
              <span class="text-[#8B949E] italic">// 2. Overtime pay</span><br/>
              otPay = otRate * otHours<br/>
              &nbsp;<br/>
              <span class="text-[#8B949E] italic">// 3. Total weekly gross</span><br/>
              regularPay = hourlyRate * 40<br/>
              total = regularPay + otPay
            </code>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-bg border border-b1 rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm">
          <h3 class="text-[15px] font-semibold text-t1 mb-3">Who qualifies for overtime?</h3>
          <ul class="flex flex-col gap-2.5">
            <li class="flex gap-2.5 text-sm text-t2 leading-relaxed items-start">
              <span class="w-3.5 h-3.5 mt-1 text-green shrink-0">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
              </span>
              Hourly workers covered by the FLSA
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-2.5 text-sm text-t2 leading-relaxed items-start">
              <span class="w-3.5 h-3.5 mt-1 text-green shrink-0">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
              </span>
              Salaried employees earning under $684/week
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-2.5 text-sm text-t2 leading-relaxed items-start">
              <span class="w-3.5 h-3.5 mt-1 text-green shrink-0">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
              </span>
              Nurses, truck drivers, warehouse workers
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-2.5 text-sm text-t2 leading-relaxed items-start">
              <span class="w-3.5 h-3.5 mt-1 text-green shrink-0">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
              </span>
              Part-time workers past the threshold
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
